                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">803.0146/598: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Charge in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-31T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 31, 1938—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Department’s 498, December 19, 3 p.m.<note n="86" xml:id="d72fn86">
                        <ref target="frus1937v03#pg_822">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1937, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 822</ref>.</note> The Brigade
                    Headquarters of the Second Marine Brigade and the Sixth Regiment of United
                    States Marines which were sent from San Diego to Shanghai in August last for
                    temporary duty as a reenforcement to the Fourth <pb facs="0066" n="62"
                        xml:id="pg_62"/> Marine Regiment already there, are to be withdrawn and are
                    due to sail from Shanghai on board the Navy transport <hi rend="italic"
                        >Chaumont</hi> on February 18.</p>
                <p>Please informally inform the Foreign Office of the foregoing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
